AWS S3 is a regional service not global. the data is physically stored in that region's data centers. 
AWS automatically replicates data across mutliple Availability Zones within that region , but not across regions by default.
S3 also supports SSL for secure data transfer and data encryption.
you can also control access to the data using IAM and also specify object permissions using s3 policies. 
